cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use SafeTune in research, please cite the main paper below."
title: "SafeTune: A Unified Library for Preserving and Restoring Safety in Fine-Tuned LLMs"
abstract: >-
  SafeTune is a library of LLM-safety methods, audited honestly
  against their cited papers. It covers train-time (harden), weight-space
  (recover, unlearn), and inference-time (steer) interventions, plus
  diagnosis (interpret) and evaluation (evaluate). Every method is audited
  against its cited paper and carries a faithfulness badge.
